const items = [
  {
    id:       'experiment-1',
    category: 'EXPERIMENT',
    title:    '[Experiment Name]',
    meta:     '[Tech] · [Year]',
    body: [
      'Placeholder — describe an experiment here. What were you testing? What was the constraint you gave yourself? The most interesting lab work comes from a single unusual restriction: one unusual input, one novel output, or one forbidden approach.',
      'What worked? What did not? Lab work is allowed to fail — in fact, experiments that fail teach more than ones that succeed on the first attempt. Describe the failure honestly and what it revealed about the problem space.',
      'Is this live? Is there a demo? A repo? If so, link it here. If not, describe what would be needed to take it from experiment to something shippable. Replace this placeholder with your actual experiment.',
    ],
    topics: ['The Constraint', 'What Failed', 'Where It Stands'],
  },
  {
    id:       'experiment-2',
    category: 'EXPERIMENT',
    title:    '[Experiment Name]',
    meta:     '[Tech] · [Year]',
    body: [
      'Placeholder — a second experiment. This one could be a shader, a generative system, a physics simulation, or a weird CSS trick. The best lab experiments are the ones where you are genuinely unsure what the output will look like before you start.',
      'What was the unexpected result? Experiments often produce outputs you did not anticipate — sometimes better, sometimes stranger, sometimes both. That moment of surprise is often worth documenting more than the intended outcome.',
      'What does this experiment demonstrate about how you approach creative coding? Update this placeholder with your actual experiment and make it specific — the technology, the constraint, and the result.',
    ],
    topics: ['The Setup', 'The Surprise', 'What It Shows'],
  },
  {
    id:       'experiment-3',
    category: 'EXPERIMENT',
    title:    '[Experiment Name]',
    meta:     '[Tech] · [Year]',
    body: [
      'Placeholder — a third experiment. Interactive audio, data visualisation, machine learning in the browser, generative art. The medium does not matter as long as the constraint is clear and the question is specific.',
      'What did building this teach you about the medium? Sometimes an experiment reveals a limitation of a tool or a browser API. Sometimes it reveals a new technique that ends up in production work. What did this one reveal?',
      'Status: ongoing, archived, or turned into a product? Some experiments stay experiments. Some grow into something you ship. Describe where this one stands. Replace this placeholder with your actual work.',
    ],
    topics: ['The Medium', 'What It Revealed', 'Current Status'],
  },
  {
    id:       'experiment-4',
    category: 'EXPERIMENT',
    title:    '[Experiment Name]',
    meta:     '[Tech] · [Year]',
    body: [
      'Placeholder — a fourth experiment. This space is for the work that does not fit anywhere else. The strange, the speculative, the one that took three weekends and you are still not sure it works but you cannot stop thinking about it.',
      'What makes this one different from the others? If your other experiments were about technique, this one might be about concept. If your others were about code, this one might be about material or form.',
      'Three weekends in, what did you learn? Not just about the technology — about yourself as a maker. The best lab notes capture the honest intellectual experience of the experiment, not just the technical outcome. Update this placeholder.',
    ],
    topics: ['The Outlier', 'Technique vs. Concept', 'The Real Lesson'],
  },
